net.sourceforge.stripes.ajax
Class JavaScriptResolution

java.lang.Object
  net.sourceforge.stripes.ajax.JavaScriptResolution
All Implemented Interfaces:
Resolution
public class JavaScriptResolution
extends Object
implements Resolution

Resolution that will convert a Java object web to a web of JavaScript objects and arrays, and stream the JavaScript back to the client. The output of this resolution can be evaluated in JavaScript using the eval() function, and will return a reference to the top level JavaScript object. For more information see JavaScriptBuilder

Since:
Stripes 1.1
Author:
Tim Fennell

JavaScriptResolution

public JavaScriptResolution(Object rootObject,
                            Object... objectsToExclude)
Constructs a new JavaScriptResolution that will convert the supplied object to JavaScript.

Parameters:
rootObject - an Object of any type supported by JavaScriptBuilder. In most cases this will either be a JavaBean, Map, Collection or Array, but may also be any one of the basic Java types including String, Date, Number etc.
objectsToExclude - Classes and/or property names to exclude from the output.
